This paper deals with coding theory and its applications in storage systems, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The paper also discusses the use of codes in distributed storage systems, which could be classified under Distributed Systems (cs.DS) or Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of codes in cloud implementations, which could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
